<HEADLINE> Egypt Calls for Solution to Iraqi Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
Saturday called for a solution to the Iraqi crisis, the Middle
East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The international community should make further efforts to
resolve the crisis, Mubarak said in an interview with the local
daily Al-Akhbar.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that military operations against Iraq would
aggravate the tension in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The current crisis came as Iraq denied the access of arms
inspectors of the United Nations Special Commission in charge of
eliminating Iraq's weapons of mass destruction to presidential
palaces for reasons of national sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The United States has threatened to launch military strikes to
force Iraqi compliance with the U.N. Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak appealed to the Iraqi leadership to comply with the
U.N. Security Council resolutions for the interests of the Iraqi
people while saying that it is not appropriate to launch a
military attack on Iraq now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
