<HEADLINE> Blair Urges West to Get Ready for Military Action on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair today branded Iraqi President Saddam Hussein an "evil
dictator" and urged the West to get ready to take military action
against him.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said Saddam's games and attempts to divide
the UN Security Council "could not be continued much longer."
</P>
<P>
"Diplomacy stands no chance of success at all unless he knows
that if he fails to listen to reason, we have the force to back it
up," Blair told a meeting of his ruling Labor Party.
</P>
<P>
Saddam had to be stopped from hanging on to his weapons of mass
destruction and a diplomatic solution was not the only option to
stop him, he warned.
</P>
<P>
He added Britain and its allies would continue to look for
every way possible to find a diplomatic solution to the crisis
over Iraq's refusal to allow U.N. weapons inspectors free access
to suspected arms sites.
</P>
<P>
"It is vital for us to stop this evil dictator hanging on to
his remaining weapons of mass destruction or acquiring more," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
