<HEADLINE> World Bank to Grant Egypt Soft Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has decided to
grant 960 million U.S. dollars of soft loans to Egypt in the
coming 18 months, the Middle East News Agency (MENA) reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The loans would be used to develop hospitals, to train doctors,
to improve infrastructure projects, irrigation system, to modernize
agriculture and to fund new projects in southern Egypt, Khaled
Ikram, head of World Bank's Egyptian Department, told MENA.
</P>
<P>
Ikram said the loans were also intended to enhance the skills
of the personnel in industry, combat industrial pollution in Cairo
and improve irrigation and drainage system in the eastern Nile
Delta region. 
</P>
