<HEADLINE> De Clercq Wins Cyclocross Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Mario de Clercq beat
pre-race favourite Richard Groenendall of the Netherlands to win
the world elite cyclocross championship in Middelfart, Denmark, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
De Clercq finished more than a minute clear of teammate Erwin
Vervecken after a solo ride of more than 18 kilometers in the
28.8km race.
</P>
<P>
Groenendaal, winner of the World Cup and Super Prestige series,
dropped out of contention in the final nine kilometers on the
frost-hardened ground.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Daniele Pontoni, who had to pass a dope test
before being allowed to start, was always among the contenders but
was beaten for the bronze by Denmark's Henrik Djernis.
</P>
<P>
It was De Clercq's second title of the weekend.  
</P>
