<HEADLINE> Pakistan, India Exchange Seized Boats, Launches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and India have
exchanged 48 fishing boats and launches recently under an
agreement signed last year, a spokesman for Fisheries Cooperative
Society (FCS) said in Karachi on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The exchange of the launches was held on the international
borders in Arabian Sea under the surveillance of Maritime Security
Agency (MSA) of Pakistan and Indian CoastGuard, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
During a recent visit to India, the Pakistani delegation
declined to accept 12 launches which were in dilapidated
condition.
</P>
<P>
Indian authorities also turned back four launches which were in
battered shape and now berthed in Karachi Port, according to the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
These fishing boats and launches had been seized by India and
Pakistan during the last few years for violating their respective
sea limits.  
</P>
