<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Benefits From Foreign Expertise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Fuzhou Mawei Shipyard, a
century-old vessel manufacturer in Fuzhou, capital of Fujian
Province, has become a major exporter in this east China province,
with the help of foreign experts.
</P>
<P>
The shipyard is one of the local institutions that have
benefited from the province's strategy to introduce more foreign
expertise to boost the local development.
</P>
<P>
Fujian introduced more than 1,500 foreign experts in the last
seven years, and 513 projects have been launched in the province.
Three-fourth of the projects are in agriculture, key projects and
high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture has been given top priority for foreign expertise
by the local government. Since 1993, Japanese experts have been
invited to give on-the-spot instruction on growing high-yield rice
paddies.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Japanese technology has been spread on more than
800,000 hectares of paddy fields to increase the output by 705
kilograms per hectare, which has resulted in an increase of more
than 1 billion yuan (120 million US dollars) for local farmers.
</P>
</TEXT>
