<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Outlines China's Priority Sectors for Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, SWITZERLAND, February 1 (Xinhua) -- China will increase
investment in priority sectors like agricultural infrastructure,
transport facilities, and environment protection projects, Chinese
Vice Premier Li Lanqing said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Talking with leaders from the media at the annual meeting of
the World Economic Forum, Li outlined China's priority sectors for
investment.
</P>
<P>
Main sectors needing further investment include irrigation and
water supply facilities and other agricultural infrastructure;
construction of railways, highways and transport facilities in
both urban and rural areas; environmental protection projects;
development of high-tech industries, technological upgrading of
enterprises; housing sector development and the development of
mid-western areas.
</P>
<P>
He believes that the rise in investment will no doubt generate
an expansion in employment and consumer demand. 
</P>
