<HEADLINE> Former England Goalkeeper Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Former Arsenal and England
goalkeeper George Marks, who once commanded a world record
transfer fee of 5,000 pounds, has died in hospital at the age of
82.
</P>
<P>
Marks made his Arsenal debut in 1939 and went on to win a
Football League Cup with Arsenal in 1943. He also played eight
times for England in wartime internationals in the same team as
Stanley Matthews, Denis Compton and Tommy Lawton.
</P>
<P>
Marks was signed by his former Arsenal teammate Eddie Hapgood,
who became Blackburn manager in 1944, for a then record fee for a
goalkeeper of 5,000 pounds.
</P>
<P>
He retiring from the professional game in 1954. 
</P>
