<HEADLINE> Foreign-Funded Firms Become Big Tax Source In Eastern Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-funded enterprises
have become a major tax source in east China's Jiangsu Province,
according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 these firms contributed 5.357 billion yuan (645 million
US dollars) in value-added and consumer taxes, up 39.32 percent
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The sum of the two taxes paid by foreign-funded companies in
1997 accounted for 17 percent of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the province had 34,000 foreign-funded
companies with an actual overseas capital of 27 billion U.S.
dollars. Of the world's top 500 firms, 165 have invested in
Jiangsu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
