<HEADLINE> Guangdong CPPCC Suggests More Cooperation With Hong Kong, Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 1 (Xinhua) -- How to promote all-around
cooperations and exchanges among China's southern province of
Guangdong, Hong Kong and Macao became a hot topic for members of
the Guangdong Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
At the first session of the Eighth CPPCC Guangdong Provincial
Committee that was held recently, participants set forth many
pertinent opinions on this issue. They also urged a higher level
of cooperation between Guangdong and the two regions with the
return of Hong Kong and Macao's imminent return.
</P>
<P>
Some Hong Kong and Macao members said an improving investment
environment and legal system as well as true national treatment to
investors will make them more confident about the province.
</P>
<P>
Since the reform and opening-up drive was launched in late
1970s, Guangdong has entered its "golden age" of economic
growth. Overseas funds worth over 81 billion U.S. dollars have
been introduced into the province, with 80 percent of that from
Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
As many Guangdong CPPCC members from Hong Kong and Macao are
investors in the province, they encouraged the provincial
government to continue introducing funds to maintain its fast
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Referring to high-tech development, they said, it is vital to
restructure industries and upgrade products in the province, and
to encourage such high-tech industries as electronic information.
</P>
<P>
