<HEADLINE> Markets Grow Steadily in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Markets of various kinds
continue to expand, in a stable and healthy manner, in east
China's Zhejiang Province in the past year, according to the
provincial administration on industry and commerce.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the province had established 4,488
marketplaces, 2.28 percent up over the previous year. Of them, 79
were productive means markets such as those dealing in real
estate, labor and intermediate agencies.
</P>
<P>
Last year, local commodity markets saw a total trading volume
of 279.8 billion yuan, up 9.93 percent year-on-year, while the
total transactions of local productive means markets reached 6.27
billion yuan, increasing by 20.07 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, local authorities made great efforts to improve the
quality of markets by standardizing market activities and stepping
up macro-control over them so as to ensure their orderly
development.
</P>
<P>
Some markets that had failed to attract dealers and buyers were
closed down by the authorities, and, on the other hand, a number
of modern markets were built up in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
