<DOCNO> XIE19980201.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Poor Decreasing in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1.1 million of the
rural poor in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality have risen
above the poverty line and are leading better lives because of
effective poverty relief measures.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing once was a city in southwest China's Sichuan
Province, but became the country's fourth municipality last March.
</P>
<P>
This young municipality has 21 poverty-stricken counties, with
a poor population of 3.66 million who are mainly living along the
Yangtze River and in the mountainous regions of Wuling and Daba
mountains. Transportation is inconvenient in these areas and the
agricultural infrastructure is backward.
</P>
<P>
To help more poor people lead better lives, the municipal
government mobilized more than 200 government departments and
institutions to form 21 separate poverty relief teams. Each team
was assigned tasks and goals in helping a specific
poverty-stricken county.
</P>
<P>
By the end of November, the poverty relief teams had helped
raise 230 million yuan for the poverty-hit areas, local sources
said. They also started 281 poverty-relief projects and helped
build 20 Project Hope primary schools.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has also adhered to the practice of executing
poverty relief work through development projects, and has
intensified construction of the agricultural infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, the municipality has invested 500 million yuan
in building roads, taming rivers, constructing power
stations, improving soil conditions and growing trees in these
areas.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Chongqing has vigorously spread application of
agronomics in its impoverished rural areas. Last year it sponsored
66 training courses for 6,000 poor farmers and spread the use of
70 practical farming techniques.
</P>
<P>
Advanced agricultural techniques have now become major factors
for poor farmers in the municipality to increase output and
income. Science and technology are credited with 40 percent of the
municipality's increased agricultural output.
</P>
<P>
Different areas have also grown many cash crops in accordance
with local conditions and engaged in processing businesses to
increase added value, said local sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980201.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Urged to Stop Interfering in Other Nations' Internal Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- China today urged the United
States to stop using the pretext of the human rights issue to
interfere in the other countries' internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
When Asked to comment on the part concerning China in the
recent human rights report issued by the US State Department,
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said that the US
government should respect the facts and abide by the norms of the
international laws.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has always respected the general purpose
of promoting and protecting human rights and basic freedom in the
United Nations Charter and the relevant international human rights
instruments on human rights, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
In conformity with the universal principles and China's
specific conditions, he said, the Chinese government has made big
efforts to realize the people's rights of subsistence and
development, kept improving the people's standards in enjoying
their political, economic, social and cultural rights while
protecting their rights of citizens and political rights in
accordance with law.
</P>
<P>
These efforts have brought about the unprecedented, all-round
improvement and continuous development of the people's human
rights conditions in China, Zhu noted.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, in disregard of the above-mentioned facts,
the US government, passing itself as the "guard of human rights,"
made irresponsible comments and fabricated unwarranted charges
upon China's human rights conditions while not uttering a single
word about cases of seriously violating human rights in its own
country.
</P>
<P>
"This is a typical example of applying dual standards on human
rights issue," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Obviously, he went on, "the real motive of the US side is to
interfere in China's internal affairs on the pretext of caring
about China's human rights."
</P>
<P>
"We hereby express our firm opposition to the US act of
seriously violating the basic norms of the international
relations," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the US government should respect the facts,
abide by the norms of the international laws, and stop using the
the so-called human rights issue to meddle in other countries'
internal affairs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
