<HEADLINE> Power Supply Improves in Lhasa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Electric power supply in Lhasa,
capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, has improved because of
the completion of the first phase of a citywide electricity
network.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 25.8 million yuan (3.1 million U.S.
dollars), including 10 million yuan (1.2 million U.S. dollars)
from the Ministry of Power Industry, the project covers major
residential areas of the old city of Lhasa.
</P>
<P>
Advanced technology and criteria were introduced while
departments of the electric power industry from Shanghai
Municipality and Sichuan Province, southwest China, sent
technicians to supervise the construction.
</P>
<P>
After a quality check, more than 85 percent of the construction
was graded as excellent. The project has also laid a sound basis
for the transformation of the power supply network of the whole
city that is scheduled to be completed by the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
