<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatian Priest Murdered in Rwandan Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A Roman Catholic priest from
Croatia, father Vjeko Curic, was assassinated in Kigali Saturday
night, the office of Rwandan Capital's police has said.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian priest who was in his forties has been living in
Rwanda for over 17 years, a release of Rwanda News Agency sent
specially for Xinhua said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He was vicar of Kivumu Parish, of Kabgayi Diocese in Central
Gitarama Province of Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Kabgayi have indicated that he was very much
involved in the reconstruction of his Diocese of which he was the
treasurer.
</P>
<P>
Much of the work related to the construction of houses for the
genocide survivors and the returnee in collaboration with the
Catholic non-governmental organizations (NGOs).
</P>
<P>
He reportedly saved many lives during the 1994 genocide which
claimed about one million Tutsis and Hutus lives from the
opposition who had sought refuge at Kabgayi.
</P>
<P>
"We have no clue about the identity of the murderer," the
Kigali Police told Rwanda News Agency, adding that investigations
have already started.
</P>
<P>
It is further reported that father Curic was shot dead by a
man who was travelling with him in his vehicle near Sainte
Famille Church, located near the main city round-about.
</P>
<P>
Security forces which rushed to the site of the crime found
eight pistol bullets in the father's body.
</P>
<P>
The murder of father Curic follows that of other clergy
people: a Belgian nun, a Canadian priest, and three sisters from
the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
Although no one has been so far arrested in connection with
the murder, well-informed sources in Gitarama have indicated that
father Curic had been receiving many death threats before.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, he miraculously escaped from an assassination attempt
at his residence in Kivumu.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the local army commander had provided him with an
armed guard that was watching over his home at night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
