<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Steel Industry Growing Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has become the country's third largest steel producer,
with an output of 10.3 million tons in 1997, just behind Shanghai
and Northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial statistics bureau, Hebei's steel
works produced 740 million yuan in profits, pushing the sector the
most important pillar industry for the province. The sector, with
a sales ratio of 99 percent, is the second largest money maker of
its kind among all provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities in China.
</P>
<P>
Compared with 1992, the province doubled the output,
assets, sales revenue and profit in steel industry, the bureau
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The bureau attributed the brisk sales to the industry's
aggressive upgrading of technology since 1992. Currently, the
sector had a ratio of continuous cast of 80 percent, about 20
percent higher than the national average.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
