<HEADLINE> IMF: S.Korea Has to Continue High Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 1 (Xinhua) -- South Korea has to continue the
implementation of the high interest rates policy until its foreign
exchange market is stabilized, said Hubert Neiss, head of the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) expert team.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at Seoul Kimpol airport on Sunday, Neiss said
South Korea was still in financial crisis and has has much work to
do.
</P>
<P>
Under the IMF-imposed austerity measures, the IMF team will
hold talks with the South Korean government over macro-economic
issues.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming talks over high interest rates is expected to
be tough as South Korea reportedly wants to bring interest rates
down after it succeeded in the talks for extension of its
short-term debts in New York last week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
