<HEADLINE> More Overseas Funds Flocking to Eastern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 753 overseas funded
enterprises was established in 1997 alone, up four percentage
points from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises had a total registered capital of 1.26
billion U.S. dollars. The province has approved 10,648
overseas-funded enterprises from 88 countries and regions. With
16.16 billion U.S. dollars in registered capital, these
enterprises have absorbed 27.09 billion U.S. dollars in overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the State Administration of
Industry and Commerce, the capital arrival rate of the
foreign-funded enterprises in Zhejiang went up from 79 percent in
1996 to 83 percent in 1997, up by four percentage points. 
</P>
