<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Wants Venables to Stay as National Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- National soccer coach Terry
Venables may stay in Australia to help the national prepare for
the 2000 Olympic Games tournament, reports said in Sydney on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Venables, who is contracted to coach the national side until
the middle of this year, is at a standstill with Soccer Australia
on his future as the national coach.
</P>
<P>
Soccer Australia chairman David Hill said Sunday that he had
hoped by now to put a detailed proposal to Venables to stay as
national coach to the 2002 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The Briton's future has been in doubt after Australia failed
narrowly to make the World Cup finals. Since then he has been
linked to the Nigerian national team, English Premier league side
Everton and Glasgow giant Rangers.
</P>
<P>
Venables has arrived in Australia to take charge of the
Australian team for an international series against Chile, Japan
and South Korea, starting on Saturday in Melbourne against Chile.
</P>
</TEXT>
