<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Up to 5.78 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 1 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of
inflation moved up to 5.78 percent for the week that ended on
January 17, as prices of pulses and vegetables continued to
skyrocket, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation, based on the wholesale price index (WPI) rose by
0.05 percentage points to 5.78 percent (provisional), the highest
in last six months.
</P>
<P>
The upsurge in inflation in recent weeks has been caused mainly
by the unusual behavior of the southwest Monsoon and the severe
cold conditions sweeping the north. As a result, in the last five
weeks alone, the prices of pulses and vegetables have gone up by a
massive 14.57 percent and 16.62 percent respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
