<HEADLINE> More Than 300 Rebels Killed in Fighting in S.Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 Tamil rebels and
at least 20 army soldiers were killed in a fierce fighting in
Northern Sri Lanka early Sunday, a military spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said a large number of Liberation Tigers
of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels launched an attack on troops
stationed in Kilinochchi District in the north at 1:30 am (local
time).
</P>
<P>
Backed by artillery and aircraft, the troops repulsed the
rebels, the spokesman said. The fighting lasted till daybreak.
</P>
<P>
Latest military reports said that over 300 rebels were killed
and a large number of others wounded during the fighting.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 soldiers were killed and 86 others injured, Dewage
said. Observers here estimated that the army's casualties could be
higher.
</P>
<P>
Government troops were now in complete control of the area and
a search operation was in progress, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The latest fighting, the biggest in recent months in Sri Lanka,
took place one week after LTTE rebels mounted a bomb attack in the
central ancient city of Kandy in a bid to mar the 50th
independence day celebrations.
</P>
<P>
One day after the bombing, the Sri Lankan government announced
it outlawed the LTTE with immediate effect. The LTTE has been
fighting for an independent state of their own in the north and
east for more than 14 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
