<HEADLINE> China Provides Better Legal System, Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, SWITZERLAND, January 31 (Xinhua) -- China's improved
legal system and investment environment have brought good returns
to both foreign investors and China itself, Chinese Vice Premier
Li Lanqing said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"As a result, China has, for the past 20 years or so, absorbed
a total of 220 billion U.S. dollars of direct foreign investment,"
Li told a panel session on China Economy of the ongoing annual
meeting of the World Economic Forum.
</P>
<P>
China has become the world's second largest recipient of direct
foreign investment, next only to the United States.
</P>
<P>
"Opening up is our long-term state policy," Li said. "We are
going to apply more favorable policies from January 1 this year
for equipment import to China by foreign investors. We welcome
more foreign investment in China."
</P>
<P>
With sustained development of industry and service sectors,
China's economy has turned "from a shortage economy to a buyer's
market" with a good supply of goods, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He also talked about the difficulties and challenges China is
facing, such as further economic restructuring and enterprise
reform.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that there exist problems during the transition
from the traditional planned economy to a socialist market one.
</P>
<P>
"However, we have gained rich experience through years of
reform," Li said. "We are confident that this difficult goal will
be reached by deepening the reform." 
</P>
</TEXT>
