systems" and "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" in practice
since the region's return to China last July, Li noted here.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to the effective leadership and management of the
present Hong Kong government, Hong Kong has enjoyed social
stability with ever growing public confidence," he told a panel
session of the annual World Economic Forum meeting.
</P>
<P>
On the Asian financial crisis's impact, Li said Hong Kong will
be able to keep the adverse effects to the minimum, given its
sound economic fundamentals, tight financial supervision and
regulation, abundant foreign exchange reserves and prompt and
proper measures by the Hong Kong government.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proven that as long as China maintains a steady
economic growth, Hong Kong will be able to maintain its prosperity
and stability," the vice premier said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government is fully supportive of the work and
measures of the present Hong Kong government to maintain Hong
Kong's financial stability and the Hong Kong dollar pegged to the
U.S. dollar," Li said. "We are confident of Hong Kong's future."
