crisis and asserted that the future is bright for the region.
</P>
<P>
"I disagree with the notion of 'Asian pessimism,' just as I
used to disagree with the idea that the next century will be
the 'Asian century,'" Li said at the World Economic Forum here.
</P>
<P>
"I believe," he told hundreds of participants at a panel
session on China Economy as part of the forum's annual meeting,
"Asia still has a bright future after reform and readjustment."
</P>
<P>
