<P>
Mokhehle said in a messagee read on his behalf by Deputy Prime
Minister Pakalitha Mosisili that he had been instructed by his
doctors to rest for a few days before resuming work.
</P>
<P>
He reportedly received medical treatment at a hospital in
Bloemfontein, South Africa, last week.
</P>
<P>
The LCD's delegates are discussing preparations for the
mountain kingdom's upcoming general election, scheduled for late
April and early May, and the local government elections later.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle had earlier announced that he did not intend
contesting the premiership in the general election.
</P>
<P>
"Even if I can continue working with the LCD leadership the
party should allocate me any other duties, aware that my time to
go has arrived," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
