<HEADLINE> Average Life Expectancy In Xinjiang On The Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Life expectancy for people in
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region is now up to 63
years, today's "People's Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
This means a real forward step from the figure of only 30 years
in the early years after liberation, the newspaper quoted sources
from the regional health bureau as saying.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang now has more than 100,000 people working in the field
of medicine, including over 10,000 doctors and health care workers
working in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
With better medical equipment and more health care workers,
Xinjiang has effectively halted the spread of various kinds of
infectious diseases like plague, cholera, and hepatitis.  
