<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Joppy Reclaims WBA Middleweight Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- American William Joppy beat
fellow countryman Julio Cesar Green on unanimous decision in
Tampa, Florida, on Saturday to reclaim his World Boxing
Association middleweight title.
</P>
<P>
The three judges scored the fight 117-113, 117-112 and 117-110
in Joppy's favor.
</P>
<P>
Joppy started fast, staggering Green in the first round with a
straight left and put together a series of uppercuts during the
fifth round.
</P>
<P>
Green was making his first defense since taking the title away
from Joppy last August.
</P>
<P>
Joppy now improved to his record to 25 wins while Green dropped
to 22 victories and three losses. 
</P>
