<HEADLINE> Olympics to Include Star Class Yachting, Women's Pentathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Star class yacht racing and
women's pentathlon will be included in the 2000 Olympic Games in
Sydney, Australia, the International Olympic Committee officials
said in Nagano, Japan, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But the Sydney Olympics organizers said in order to maintain
the limitation on the number of the overall competitors, entries
for some other events have to be cut.
</P>
<P>
The normal 32-strong entry for men's modern pentathlon has been
halved and the same number will contest the women's event, while
reductions would have to be made to other yachting categories to
keep the number of sailors to a limit of around 400. 
</P>
