academics and customary chiefs, at Bukavu in the east of the
Democratic Republic of Congo, the Kinshasa-based human rights
group AZADHO said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- A total of 194 Kenyans have died across the country since
the El Nino-related rains started in October while nearly 50,000
other people have been displaced and about 31,000 livestock
killed, according to the National Operations Center. 
