<HEADLINE> Thailand Hopes to Open New Tourism Route to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Tourism Authority of
Thailand (TAT) is hoping to pioneer a new overland route linking
northern Thailand and southern China in order to boost Thailand's
tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
TAT Governor Seree Wangpaichitr was quoted Sunday by local
press as saying that at the moment Chinese tourists can only visit
Thailand through designated airports.
</P>
<P>
He said if the land route is opened, there will be a big influx
of Chinese coming to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
He said traveling by road is the best way to see the region.
</P>
<P>
About half a million Chinese visited Thailand in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The governor said he expected an increase of 15 percent this
year, due mainly to the sharp appreciation of the Chinese currency
yuan against Thailand's beleaguered baht, which has lost more than
half its value in the past seven months.  
</P>
