<HEADLINE> Thai Education Ministry Moves to Curb School Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Believing drug abuse among
students is close to national-crisis level, Thailand's Education
Ministry is pushing for a stringent anti-drug policy in schools
nationwide, according to local press Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Education Minister Sonsak Prisnananthakul was quoted as
saying that the proposal would go before the cabinet for approval
this month.
</P>
