national priority to be taken up by the current and future
government, Sonsak said.
</P>
<P>
One white school measure is to introduce drug testing in
schools.
</P>
<P>
"The ministry will push the policy to be adopted as a long-term
policy, not a temporary measure that fades away when the country
has a new government," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sonsak insisted that drug tests are needed to assess the extent
of the problem. "It's alarming when unfounded reports were
released that about five million Thai kids are drug addicts," he
said.  
