<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier: Asia Has Bright Future in 21st Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, SWITZERLAND, January 31 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice
Premier Li Lanqing said here Saturday that he expected a bright
future for Asia in the new 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Li was speaking at a panel session on China Economy at the
ongoing annual meeting of the World Economic Forum. Hundreds of
participants attended the session.
</P>
<P>
"I disagree with the notion of 'Asian pessimism,' just as I
disagree with the idea that the next century will be the 'Asian
century,'" Li said at the Davos Congress Center.
</P>
<P>
"I believe Asia still has a bright future after reform and
readjustment," he said.
</P>
<P>
The 21st century will be full of challenges and opportunities,
Li said, adding he hopes it will also be a new century of peace,
stability and common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"To realize the aspiration, we have no other option but to
strengthen cooperation among all countries and nations on the
basis of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should utilize the valuable resources on earth in a more
effective way and better protect this shared home of ours."
</P>
<P>
The vice premier also promised that China is ready to make its
contribution to the realization of this goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
