<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAS to Meet on Electoral Contributions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The "Meeting of Government
Representatives on Electoral Contributions," called by the
Organization of American States (OAS), is scheduled to be held
here on February 16 and 17.
</P>
<P>
Delegates and experts from the 34 OAS member countries will
exchange experience on how to develop internal guidelines to
regulate the contributions to electoral campaigns and to limit
their cost.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is to analyze the factors that make difficult the
control of such contributions, in relation to the amount, the
origin of the funds, and the fairness in the allotment of funds
for the political organizations.
</P>
<P>
Alternate ways will also be explored to coordinate efforts and
develop the mechanisms of international cooperation in the
allotment of funds for the political organizations.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan Foreign Affairs Ministry said in a press
release that the infiltration of illicit money to finance
electoral campaigns and political parties is becoming a common
problem in the countries of this hemisphere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
