<HEADLINE> Chile Rejects U.S. Report on Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Acting Interior
Minister Belisario Velasco Friday rejected a United States report
alleging that Chilean police abuse and maltreatment in prisons.
</P>
<P>
He dismissed the report made by the United States which
"forgets the violations committed in that country."
</P>
<P>
The report made by the U.S. State Department contains contents
not related to reality, he said, adding that in Chile "human
rights are generally respected."
</P>
<P>
"It is a policy of the Chilean government absolutely to respect
the human rights," the minister said. 
</P>
