<HEADLINE> Cuba Allocates More Money for Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban government has
increased its 1998 budget for education by three percent to 1.15
billion pesos (1.15 billion U.S. dollars), Education Minister Luis
Ignacio Gomez said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said that the budget will guarantee a job and a salary for
the country's 250,000 teachers, as well as those graduating
teachers.
</P>
<P>
A school refurbishing program will also be implemented to
benefit more than 2,200 schools across the country. The program
will also cover day care centers.
</P>
<P>
The increased budget showed again the great attention the
government has attached to education, Gomez said.
</P>
<P>
Cuba provides free education to students at all
levels. Education is also one of the sectors which is completely
barred from foreign investment and subsidized by the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
