<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Grain Production Increases in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The output of cereals, legumes
and oil-bearing seeds amounted to 77.67 million tons in 1997, up
5.51 percent from the 73.61 million tons of 1996, the Brazilian
Geography and Statistics Institute said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Grain output in the major agrarian areas in southern and
eastern Brazil increased by 6.69 percent, accounting for 89
percent of the country's total, the institute said.
</P>
<P>
It said, however, that grain production in other regions
dropped by 3.72 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural Minister Arlindo Porto said he expected this
year's grain production to be excellent.
</P>
<P>
Soybean harvest will be 30.4 million tons compared with 26.1
million tons in 1997, and rice output is expected to be 9.9
million tons, which is 0.4 million tons more than that of 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
