<HEADLINE> China Southern Airlines Eyes Bigger Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 1 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines, one of
the nation's major airlines based in Guangzhou City, plans to gain
a greater share of the air transportation market both at home and
abroad..
</P>
<P>
Liu yanxiang, General Manager of China Southern's Shanghai
Service Company, noted that China Southern ranked 23rd amongst the
top 30 airlines belonging to the International Air Transport
Association in 1997.
</P>
<P>
China Southern now operates a fleet of more than 70 Boeing
and Airbus aircraft on 270 domestic and international routes. It
handled over 12 million passengers during 1997, according to Liu.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that the company has ordered six Boeing 777s which
will fly regularly scheduled routes out of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The company also plans to expand its service network, said Liu,
adding that the company's new ticket offices in downtown Shanghai
offer 24 hour service.
</P>
<P>
China Southern also raised over six billion yuan in development
funds from 1997 stock listings in Hong Kong and New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
