<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy, France Worried About Situation in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano
Prodi and French President Jacques Chirac talked on the telephone
and expressed on Saturday "serious worries" about the situation in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said: "We decided to stay in constant contact and we
agreed that every diplomatic channel should be followed before any
other action is considered."
</P>
<P>
Paris warned Iraq on Friday that it faced "very grave
consequences" unless it allowed U.N. inspections of suspected
weapons sites to resume.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile in London, U.S. Secretary of State Albright confirmed
that America wanted to pursue diplomacy as far as was possible.
</P>
<P>
She stressed however that "diplomatic possibilities are getting
smaller." 
</P>
</TEXT>
