<HEADLINE> Beijing Financial Sector Opens Wider </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The financial sector in
Beijing, the Chinese capital, will open wider to foreign banks
during 1998, according to Lu Xueyong, president of the Beijing
Branch of the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a recent financial conference, Lu said the city will
approve more branches of foreign banks and will use substantially
more foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
The business scope of foreign banks is expected to expand
significantly, according to Lu.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the municipal government approved five branches of
foreign banks from the United States, Australia, France and
Singapore, with the total number of related facilities rising to
14.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the 20 representative offices for foreign financial
institutions established in the city during 1997 raised the total
number of related offices to 222.  
</P>
</TEXT>
