<HEADLINE> Cuba To Be Absent From Fencing World Cup Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Cuba will be absent from the
Fencing World Cup Tournament, which started in Bogota on Saturday,
for economic reasons, the Cuban Fencing Federation announced.
</P>
<P>
The Bogota world championships will be attended by some 50 epee
handlers from 16 teams of Germany, Chile, Australia, Mexico,
Switzerland, Ecuador, the United States, Panama, Guatemala,
Argentina, Estonia, the Netherlands, Spain, Portugal, Ireland, and
Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Being Paced by World Cup champion Ivan Trebejo, the Cuban team
also included besides Carlos Perdomo, Nelson Loyol Camilo Boris,
Cesar Aguilera, and Gisel Goneo, will take part in the Ramon Fonst
in Memoriam Tournament, to be held here on February 7 and 8.
</P>
<P>
After taking part in the Fonst Tournament, the Antillians will
compete in the Barcelona, Spain, and Glasgow, England,
tournaments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
