<HEADLINE> Briton Oliver Keeps European Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Spencer Oliver of Britain beat
French challenger Fabrice Benichou to retain his European
junior-featherweight title here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Oliver, 22, stopped the French in the fourth round of the
scheduled 12-round bout, stretching his record to 14 wins.
</P>
<P>
Benichou, 32, was floored for counts in both the second and
third rounds.
</P>
<P>
The referee had no hesitation to stop the bout when Benichou
dropped again in the fourth.
</P>
<P>
Benichou has now been beaten 17 times in 64 contests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
