<HEADLINE> Brodie Keeps Commonwealth Boxing Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Michael Brodie retained his
British and Commonwealth super-bantamweight titles here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Challenger Brian Carr of Scotland was pulled out in the 10th
round because of bad cuts over both his eyes.
</P>
<P>
Brodie could have had finished the game earlier if he had not
suffered from several excellent combinations from Carr in the
seventh round.
</P>
<P>
Carr, unbeaten before the fight, was first cut in the fourth
round and by the tenth round his eyebrows were bleeding, prompting
the referee to stop the bout. 
</P>
