<HEADLINE> Qingdao Expands Downtown District </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A new downtown area has emerged
in the eastern section of Qingdao, an east China coastal city
famous for its beautiful beaches and beer.
</P>
<P>
A formerly undeveloped area covering 3.7 million sq.m. in the
outskirts of the city has rapidly emerged as a magnet for
investment from both at home and abroad. The area is now home to
some 50 structures with 20 floors or more.
</P>
<P>
Fifty percent of construction projects covering 1.8 million
sq.m. were completed by the end of last year at a cost of 7.6
billion yuan (915 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A number of large real estate projects, including the
Shangri-La Hotel, a major shopping mall and various commercial
centers were completed by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure construction has maintained the pace of urban
expansion, with the completion of road stretching 16 km. and the
renovation of pipelines running 132 kilometers. The city has also
reclaimed some 49 ha. of coastal land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
