<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Space Shuttle Returns to Earth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- After completing its
nine-day mission, the U.S. space shuttle Endeavor landed at the
Kennedy Space Center in Florida at 5:35 p.m. (local time) today.
</P>
<P>
With seven crew members, the space shuttle landed on the
concrete runway on time. The home-sick astronaut David Wolf was
greeted by his mother and his friends. After his stay for four
months in the space, Wolf has to undergo intensive medical tests
and weeks of rehabilitation. His bones and muscles were weakened
in weightlessness, and his immune system and sense of balance
altered.
</P>
<P>
During its five-day docking with the Russian Mir station,
aparting from delivering supply goods to the Russian Mir station,
Endeavor had delivered astronaut Andrew Thomas and picked up
astronaut Wolf.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of docking is to give the two countries practice
working together before the assembling of the international space
station later this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
